{{Infobox Journal | title = International Journal of Applied Philosophy | cover = Ijapcover3.gif | editor = Elliot D. Cohen | discipline = [[Applied philosophy]], [[ethics]] | abbreviation = Int. J. Appl. Philos. | publisher = [[Philosophy Documentation Center]] | country = United States | frequency = Biannually | history = 1982–present | website = https://www.pdcnet.org/ijap | link2 = https://www.pdcnet.org/ijap/toc | link2-name = Online access | OCLC = 9693598 | JSTOR = | LCCN = 83-645132 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0739-098X | eISSN = 2153-6910 }} The '''''International Journal of Applied Philosophy''''' is a biannual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes philosophical examinations of practical problems. It was established in 1982, and contains original articles, reviews, and edited discussions of topics of general interest in ethics and applied philosophy. The journal is published by the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]], and some articles are published in co-operation with the [[Association for Practical and Professional Ethics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdcnet.org/ijap |title=Journal web site |accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref>
==Subject coverage== The journal covers issues in [[business]], [[education]], the [[Social environment|environment]], [[government]], [[health care]], [[law]], [[psychology]], and [[science]]. Special issue topical coverage has included [[abortion]], [[animal rights]], [[gambling]], [[Lie|lying]], [[terrorism]], [[torture]], and the [[foreign policy of the United States]].
