'''''Resilitheca''''' is a genus of land plant known from kidney-shaped sporangia.<ref name="Edwards2008">{{Cite journal | last1 = Edwards | first1 = D. | last2 = Fanning | first2 = U. | last3 = Davies | first3 = K. L. | last4 = Axe | first4 = L. | last5 = Richardson | first5 = J. B. | title = Exceptional preservation in Lower Devonian coalified fossils from the Welsh Borderland: a new genus based on reniform sporangia lacking thickened borders | doi = 10.1111/j.1095-8339.1995.tb00454.x | journal = Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society | volume = 117 | pages = 233 | year = 2008 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref> It is known from [[charcoal]]ified Early Devonian deposits, its type locality being the Brown Clee Hill [[lagerstätten]].<ref name="Glasspool2006">{{Cite journal | last1 = Glasspool | first1 = I. | last2 = Edwards | first2 = D. | last3 = Axe | first3 = L. | title = Charcoal in the Early Devonian: A wildfire-derived Konservat–Lagerstätte | doi = 10.1016/j.revpalbo.2006.03.021 | journal = Review of Palaeobotany and Palynology | volume = 142 | pages = 131 | year = 2006 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>

